      <Value><![CDATA[<p><span class="lead-big">Principal Duties</span></p>
<p>Below is an outline of the duties the post holder may be asked to do. The exact balance between these duties will vary from year to year and will be agreed annually with the Head of Division.</p>
<p><strong>General </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To carry out the duties of the post in accordance with university policies and procedures;</li>
<li>To be aware of our Student Experience Strategy and to collaborate with our students as members of a community of learning in order to engender a student-centred learning experience;</li>
<li>To maintain a safe work environment, including ensuring compliance with legislation and the undertaking of risk assessments as necessary;</li>
<li>To contribute effectively to the administrative processes and committee structures of the division, school and university;</li>
<li>To maintain own continuing professional development.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Academic Leadership and Management  </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To liaise with Programme Leaders and the staff team in order to allocate teaching and administrative responsibilities to other members of staff as appropriate and in accordance with the principles of AWAM;</li>
<li>To collaborate effectively with the School Manager to ensure all operational, quality and administrative standards are maintained;</li>
<li>To liaise with Collaborative Academic Leads to ensure the effective delivery of programmes at partner institutions;</li>
<li>To collaborate with professional, statutory, and third sector bodies as necessary;</li>
<li>To manage staffing absence cover for teaching and learning activities when they arise due to sickness, research work, leave, etc.;</li>
<li>To conduct the Performance Enhancement Reviews (PER) of academic staff;</li>
<li>In consultation with the Head of Division, manage the performance of staff within the division;</li>
<li>To lead the enhancement of teaching and learning within the division, supporting staff to pursue curriculum innovation;</li>
<li>To ensure student feedback is effectively gathered and acted upon across all programmes;</li>
<li>To attend relevant UG and PG programme meetings, and representing the Division on appropriate University committees and working groups;</li>
<li>To represent the Division at external events as appropriate, supporting the division to build its external profile;</li>
<li>In collaboration with the Head of Division, Programme Leaders and Professional Services Staff ensure programmes are meeting student recruitment targets;</li>
<li>To work collaboratively with the Head of Division in undertaking division-wide administrative and quality assurance requirements;</li>
<li>In consultation with the Head of Division, ensuring the divisional budget is effectively managed and delivered;</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Teaching and Learning</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To undertake teaching and assessment at both PG and UG level, including: setting, marking and assessing coursework and examinations and provide appropriate feedback to students;</li>
<li>To regularly collect, and respond to, student feedback;</li>
<li>To contribute to the supervision of undergraduate and postgraduate dissertations;</li>
<li>To contribute to the review of modules and programmes and to quality assurance mechanisms;</li>
<li>To utilise innovative approaches to teaching and learning which includes research-led teaching;</li>
<li>To act as a personal academic tutor;</li>
<li>To undertake administrative roles relevant to the management and delivery of programmes, up to and including programme leadership;</li>
<li>To undertake other teaching-related administrative duties as appropriate.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Research, Innovation, and Impact </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>To undertake innovative and independent research;</li>
<li>To promote the integration of own research area with other research interests within and, as appropriate, outside the division, school and university;</li>
<li>To develop and maintain a record of high quality, regular and original research publications in peer reviewed journals or other appropriate outlets;</li>
<li>To seek out and attract research income on an individual and collaborative basis;</li>
<li>To be involved in doctoral supervision;</li>
<li>To develop knowledge exchange and commercialisation opportunities.</li>
<li>To undertake any other duties which may be commensurate within the role and grade as requested by the Head of Division.</li>
</ul>]]></Value>
