    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p><strong>Role Purpose</strong></p>
<p>The Associate Head of Division will support the Head of Division, working collaboratively under their guidance and steer, to manage the overall growth and health of the Division. The role holder will be either a Senior Lecturer or Reader and have delegated line management responsibility for some of the lecturing staff within the Division, which will include workload allocation and the implementation of the Performance Enhancement and Review (PER) process. The role holder will be a member of the School Management Team and ensure continuity of day-to-day operations within the Business School programmes and may assume Acting Head of Division responsibilities when the Head of Division is on leave or unavailable. With the specialist knowledge required to teach across a range of undergraduate and postgraduate management modules, they will also have wider knowledge and expertise related to one or more of the following: Business Analytics, Digital Marketing and e-Business, Organisational Strategy, and Logistics and Supply Chain Management. As part of the role, they will also be required to liaise and support colleagues at our transnational partners who deliver business management degrees.</p>]]></Value>
    </introduction>
